Megan Huntsman, 40, was today given six terms of five years to life in prison after pleading guilty to killing six of her children . 
  She strangled the newborns to death moments after they were born and then stashed their bodies in her garage in Pleasant Grove, Utah . 
  Her estranged husband found one of the bodies in the garage last year . 
  Huntsman told police she started killing the children because she was addicted to meth . 
  She was today handed six sentences of five year to life . 
  Three will be served consecutively - meaning she will spend at least 15 years in prison . 
 